
1. Create Task
Action: A user with a MANAGER or OWNER role creates a new available chore blueprint.
HTTP Endpoint: POST /api/tasks
Request Payload


{
  "id": "task-clean-garage",
  "title": "Organize and Clean Garage",
  "description": "Sweep floors, break down cardboard boxes, and rack tools.",
  "rewardPoints": 150,
  "managerId": "parent-alex",
  "requiresReview": true,
  "recurrence": "NONE"
}

Expected Response

{
  "id": "task-clean-garage",
  "title": "Organize and Clean Garage",
  "description": "Sweep floors, break down cardboard boxes, and rack tools.",
  "rewardPoints": 150,
  "managerId": "parent-alex",
  "performerId": null,
  "status": "AVAILABLE"
}

2. Claim Task

Action: A user with a PERFORMER role claims the open chore.
HTTP Endpoint: POST /api/tasks?action=claim&id=task-clean-garage&userId=child-timmy
Request Body: Leave empty


Expected Response (200 OK)
JSON
{
  "message": "Task successfully assigned to Timmy Smith",
  "task": {
    "id": "task-clean-garage",
    "title": "Organize and Clean Garage",
    "description": "Sweep floors, break down cardboard boxes, and rack tools.",
    "rewardPoints": 150,
    "managerId": "parent-alex",
    "performerId": "child-timmy",
    "status": "ASSIGNED"
  }
}

3. Submit Task for Review
Action: The assigned performer completes the work and submits it for approval.
HTTP Endpoint: POST /api/tasks?action=submit&id=task-clean-garage&userId=child-timmy
Request Body: Leave empty
Expected Response (200 OK)
JSON
{
  "message": "Task marked completed. Awaiting manager approval."
}

4. Verify Task & Release Points
Action: The manager reviews the work, closes the task, and releases the points to the child's balance.
HTTP Endpoint: POST /api/tasks?action=verify&id=task-clean-garage&userId=parent-alex
Request Body: Leave empty
Expected Response (200 OK)
JSON
{
  "message": "Task approved. Transferred 150 credits to Timmy Smith."
}

5. Final State Verification (GET Requests)
 verify the data persistence state changes on disk by sending quick GET requests to check the final statuses.
Fetch Task State (GET /api/tasks?id=task-clean-garage)
